WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.083 --> 00:00:02.208
[crowd cheering]

2
00:00:02.291 --> 00:00:04.750
[announcer] <i>Delaney with the puck!</i>
<i>He's trying to fend them off!</i>

3
00:00:04.833 --> 00:00:06.041
<i>Delaney shoots!</i>

4
00:00:06.125 --> 00:00:07.583
<i>He scores!</i>

5
00:00:07.666 --> 00:00:09.541
<i>Ransom wins!</i>

6
00:00:09.625 --> 00:00:11.875
<i>Ransom wins!</i>

7
00:00:11.958 --> 00:00:13.791
[cheers and applause]

8
00:00:14.875 --> 00:00:17.458
Hannah. Hannah.

9
00:00:18.458 --> 00:00:19.625
We won.

10
00:00:21.416 --> 00:00:23.083
[band playing percussive music]

11
00:00:27.708 --> 00:00:29.625
["This Too Shall Pass" by OK Go playing]

12
00:00:31.833 --> 00:00:34.291
<i>♪When the morning comes...♪</i>

13
00:00:34.833 --> 00:00:37.166
Uh. excuse me. gentlemen.

14
00:00:37.250 --> 00:00:40.000
The UN has declared
an international band emergency.

15
00:00:40.083 --> 00:00:42.791
and they say that my dad
is the only man for the job.

16
00:00:42.875 --> 00:00:44.375
An international band emergency?

17
00:00:44.458 --> 00:00:45.666
Have they called Prince?

18
00:00:45.750 --> 00:00:47.708
They tried. but he is famously dead.

19
00:00:47.791 --> 00:00:50.375
Good God. this is worse than I thought.

20
00:00:50.458 --> 00:00:52.041
-Sorry. guys.
-[Hannah laughs]

21
00:00:52.125 --> 00:00:53.791
You're so weird.

22
00:00:53.875 --> 00:00:56.541
Also. can we hit Dairy Queen
on the way home?

23
00:00:56.625 --> 00:01:00.416
What? Are you saying the international
band emergency was a ruse?

24
00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:02.125
Is Prince even dead?

25
00:01:02.208 --> 00:01:06.000
Han! Honey. you were phenomenal.

26
00:01:06.083 --> 00:01:08.333
Uh. how was I?

27
00:01:08.416 --> 00:01:10.416
Mm. you were okay. too.

28
00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:11.625
Ah. yes!

29
00:01:11.708 --> 00:01:13.208
[laughs]

30
00:01:13.291 --> 00:01:14.708
Okay. can I help you?

31
00:01:14.791 --> 00:01:17.875
[Greg] I just want to know
how your new song is coming along.

32
00:01:17.958 --> 00:01:19.375
[breathing heavily]

33
00:01:19.458 --> 00:01:22.250
It must be going well.
because you missed three cues tonight.

34
00:01:22.333 --> 00:01:23.791
The muse waits for no one.

35
00:01:23.875 --> 00:01:25.375
[Greg]
<i>Oh. does the muse play clarinet?</i>

36
00:01:25.750 --> 00:01:28.500
Because we're looking
for a new alternate first chair.

37
00:01:30.458 --> 00:01:32.291
[panting]

38
00:01:33.375 --> 00:01:34.416
[woman] <i>Just write. Hannah.</i>

39
00:01:34.750 --> 00:01:36.750
[breathing heavily]

40
00:01:41.250 --> 00:01:42.791
["This Too Shall Pass" playing
over headphones]

41
00:01:42.875 --> 00:01:44.125
-[knock on door]
-[Allie] Han?

42
00:01:44.208 --> 00:01:45.916
I'm gonna skip the game today.

43
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.458
Got an extra monster cookie
if you want one.

44
00:01:48.541 --> 00:01:49.833
[knocking]

45
00:01:49.916 --> 00:01:51.375
Hannah?

46
00:01:51.458 --> 00:01:52.750
Babe. you okay?

47
00:01:52.833 --> 00:01:54.250
[music stops]

48
00:01:54.333 --> 00:01:56.291
Yeah. yeah. sorry. I'm...

49
00:01:57.791 --> 00:01:59.041
I'm not super hungry.

50
00:01:59.125 --> 00:02:01.166
Uh. don't worry about me. I'm-- I'm good.

51
00:02:02.208 --> 00:02:03.625
[Allie] Okay. love you.

52
00:02:03.708 --> 00:02:05.833
[dramatic music playing]

53
00:02:09.333 --> 00:02:12.291
-[breathing heavily]
-[heart pounding]

54
00:02:16.833 --> 00:02:17.958
[breathes sharply]

55
00:02:25.416 --> 00:02:27.708
[Dean]
Look at those smug motherfuckers.

56
00:02:27.791 --> 00:02:30.125
Their ten-game streak ends now.

57
00:02:30.208 --> 00:02:32.666
[exhales] Not if their new center
has anything to say about it.

58
00:02:32.750 --> 00:02:35.125
[Dean] Please. he's been skating
in fucking cornfields.

59
00:02:35.208 --> 00:02:36.833
-Iowa. or whatever.
-[Birdie] Indiana.

60
00:02:36.916 --> 00:02:38.791
Kid's fast as fuck. Physical. too.

61
00:02:38.875 --> 00:02:40.500
Doesn't matter. Nothing's getting past us.

62
00:02:41.291 --> 00:02:43.041
[speaking Czech]

63
00:02:43.125 --> 00:02:44.416
[Dean] Yeah. see? Simms gets it.

64
00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:46.333
Yeah. come on. boys.
Let's get it.

65
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:48.583
Fuck. yeah. Let's go.

66
00:02:51.666 --> 00:02:52.541
[door closes]

67
00:02:52.625 --> 00:02:55.916
He also doesn't back down from anything.
Same as Garrett.

68
00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:58.625
Oh. shit. Papa Graham's mad early.

69
00:02:58.708 --> 00:03:00.166
No pressure. man.

70
00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:08.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

71
00:03:09.041 --> 00:03:11.333
Garrett. good to see you.

72
00:03:12.375 --> 00:03:13.666
[sighs]

73
00:03:16.375 --> 00:03:18.458
Looks like you got
a tough one out there today.

74
00:03:18.541 --> 00:03:19.875
-Feeling good?
-[door opens]

75
00:03:19.958 --> 00:03:22.166
Yeah. you know what?
Don't worry about me. I'm ready.

76
00:03:22.250 --> 00:03:24.083
Sorry. I left my phone in the car.

77
00:03:24.166 --> 00:03:25.416
It's okay.

78
00:03:25.500 --> 00:03:26.583
Hi. Garrett.

79
00:03:29.750 --> 00:03:30.833
[gasps]

80
00:03:32.291 --> 00:03:33.541
Cindy.

81
00:03:33.625 --> 00:03:34.958
Good luck out there today.

82
00:03:38.291 --> 00:03:39.833
Yeah.

83
00:03:39.916 --> 00:03:41.125
Thanks.

84
00:03:53.458 --> 00:03:55.458
[dramatic music playing]

85
00:03:58.625 --> 00:04:00.333
[cell phone vibrates]

86
00:04:08.458 --> 00:04:10.125
[vibrating continues]

87
00:04:11.458 --> 00:04:12.708
[breathes sharply]

88
00:04:15.791 --> 00:04:18.583
[Allie] Sean. I am so sorry
that you had to find out like that.

89
00:04:18.666 --> 00:04:20.708
I never meant to hurt your feelings.

90
00:04:20.791 --> 00:04:23.833
But also. literally. how dare you suggest
that I am incapable of being alone?

91
00:04:23.916 --> 00:04:27.125
Like. that's so fucked of you.
Sean. So fucked.

92
00:04:27.208 --> 00:04:28.750
Again. could not be more sorry.

93
00:04:28.833 --> 00:04:31.791
-Please just call me back or text me or--
-[voicemail beeps]

94
00:04:31.875 --> 00:04:34.791
[computerized voice]
<i>Please hang up or press one to re-record.</i>

95
00:04:38.500 --> 00:04:40.416
-Oh.
-Allie. what are you doing here?

96
00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:42.083
Uh. this is the drama building.

97
00:04:42.166 --> 00:04:44.583
I'm in the correct place.
What are you doing here?

98
00:04:44.666 --> 00:04:47.291
This is perfect. You're not busy. right?
I need a huge favor.

99
00:04:47.375 --> 00:04:50.666
No. Beau. sorry. I can't
take on anyone else's stress today.

100
00:04:50.750 --> 00:04:52.666
I am emotionally raw.
I'm the shell of a woman.

101
00:04:52.750 --> 00:04:54.916
Okay. Okay. Thank you. Ira.

102
00:04:56.583 --> 00:04:57.583
You. too. Ira.

103
00:04:58.791 --> 00:04:59.958
Bye. Ira.

104
00:05:00.500 --> 00:05:03.958
Sorry about that.
Ira is not great at ending conversations.

105
00:05:04.041 --> 00:05:05.583
Jo. this is Allie. Allie--

106
00:05:05.666 --> 00:05:06.833
You're Joanna Maxwell.

107
00:05:06.916 --> 00:05:08.000
Yeah. Allie's a fan.

108
00:05:08.791 --> 00:05:10.125
Nice to meet you.

109
00:05:10.208 --> 00:05:14.000
Wait. are you Allie Hayes?
Don't we have the same agent?

110
00:05:14.666 --> 00:05:15.958
You know who I am.

111
00:05:17.250 --> 00:05:18.833
Joanna Maxwell knows who I am.

112
00:05:18.916 --> 00:05:19.916
Well. you can just call me Jo.

113
00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:23.000
Yo. respectfully. there is literally
no way I can make that happen.

114
00:05:23.083 --> 00:05:24.875
-[chuckles]
-Joanna's back here doing a master class

115
00:05:24.958 --> 00:05:26.833
with the seniors.
because she's so famous.

116
00:05:26.916 --> 00:05:28.291
Definitely not famous.

117
00:05:28.375 --> 00:05:31.083
And because she's so famous.
she has this big self-tape.

118
00:05:31.166 --> 00:05:33.333
-It's a same-day audition.
-Last time I read with Jo.

119
00:05:33.416 --> 00:05:34.375
I got in trouble
for my voice

120
00:05:34.458 --> 00:05:36.666
-being "stiff and distracting."
-Well...

121
00:05:36.750 --> 00:05:39.208
So. I thought that maybe
you could read with her. Allie.

122
00:05:39.291 --> 00:05:42.125
so I could go do literally anything else.

123
00:05:42.208 --> 00:05:43.333
-[scoffs]
-What?

124
00:05:43.416 --> 00:05:44.375
-Beau...
-Uh-huh?

125
00:05:44.458 --> 00:05:46.083
You don't just ask someone
to be your reader.

126
00:05:46.166 --> 00:05:48.000
-There's an etiquette. fool.
-Mm-hmm.

127
00:05:48.083 --> 00:05:50.208
Sorry about him.
I couldn't ask you to do that.

128
00:05:50.291 --> 00:05:51.541
It would derail your entire day.

129
00:05:51.625 --> 00:05:55.208
No. no. no. derail it. please.
Seriously. it is not a problem.

130
00:05:55.291 --> 00:05:59.416
I would be honored
to read with <i>the </i>Joanna Maxwell.

131
00:06:03.541 --> 00:06:04.833
-[whistle blows]
-This is it. folks.

132
00:06:04.916 --> 00:06:07.208
The start of our
long-awaited game with St. A's

133
00:06:07.291 --> 00:06:09.041
and their new center. Aaron Delaney.

134
00:06:09.125 --> 00:06:11.208
[rock music playing]

135
00:06:13.708 --> 00:06:15.375
[Jules]
And we're underway here in the first.

136
00:06:15.458 --> 00:06:17.166
Hawks take possession.

137
00:06:18.208 --> 00:06:19.458
[grunts]

138
00:06:19.541 --> 00:06:20.875
-[crowd groans]
-[Jules] Oh. shit.

139
00:06:20.958 --> 00:06:22.500
Brutal hit from Aaron Delaney.

140
00:06:22.583 --> 00:06:27.208
Seems the new guy's fitting right in with
St. A's legendary trash-talking bullies.

141
00:06:27.291 --> 00:06:28.416
-[grunts]
-[crowd groans]

142
00:06:30.083 --> 00:06:32.583
-[groans]
-Whoa! How is that not a penalty?

143
00:06:32.666 --> 00:06:34.208
Hawks regain possession.

144
00:06:34.875 --> 00:06:37.166
Graham starts out
from behind his own net and...

145
00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:39.708
-Oh! Delaney says. nope.
-[crowd groans]

146
00:06:40.291 --> 00:06:41.916
[Jules]
He shoots... and beats

147
00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:43.958
Simms's blocker side
for the goal.

148
00:06:44.041 --> 00:06:45.000
[crowd jeering]

149
00:06:45.083 --> 00:06:47.333
Come on. Graham.
It's not fun if you don't fight back.

150
00:06:47.416 --> 00:06:48.666
Fuck you.

151
00:06:48.750 --> 00:06:50.958
[laughs]
Take it easy. princess.

152
00:06:51.833 --> 00:06:53.083
Whoo!

153
00:06:53.166 --> 00:06:55.166
Hey. come on. bro.

154
00:06:55.250 --> 00:06:57.625
-Shake it off. You got this.
-[crowd audio fades and distorts]

155
00:06:58.416 --> 00:07:00.041
[Garrett]
<i>Wellsy. where are you?</i>

156
00:07:17.333 --> 00:07:19.625
-[breathing heavily]
-[woman] Just write. Hannah.

157
00:07:42.166 --> 00:07:43.291
[vibrating]

158
00:07:44.375 --> 00:07:46.375
[ominous music playing]

159
00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:50.666
[breathing heavily]

160
00:07:51.708 --> 00:07:54.750
-[sniffling. gasping]
-[vibrating continues]

161
00:07:54.833 --> 00:07:57.208
-[stick hit echoes]
-[Jules] <i>Nasty cross-check by Delaney.</i>

162
00:07:57.291 --> 00:07:59.625
<i>Vipers are absolutely dominating</i>
<i>the Hawks right now.</i>

163
00:07:59.708 --> 00:08:02.041
<i>Hawks can't play the zone.</i>
<i>Vipers collect the puck</i>

164
00:08:02.125 --> 00:08:03.500
<i>in the Hawks' zone.</i>
<i>Are you kidding?</i>

165
00:08:03.583 --> 00:08:04.708
<i>The Vipers are relentless.</i>

166
00:08:04.791 --> 00:08:07.458
<i>There's is a slashing penalty</i>
<i>on St. A's 29.</i>

167
00:08:07.541 --> 00:08:09.458
-[woman] Just write. Hannah.
-<i>There's Delaney again.</i>

168
00:08:09.541 --> 00:08:11.375
<i>What the actual fuck?</i>

169
00:08:11.458 --> 00:08:12.875
<i>Delaney shoots.</i>

170
00:08:12.958 --> 00:08:14.125
[breathing heavily]

171
00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:20.458
[Jensen] Well. that wasn't
the first period I was looking for.

172
00:08:20.541 --> 00:08:22.375
Graham. Delaney's shadowing you.

173
00:08:22.458 --> 00:08:24.416
Move the puck. Look at Birdie and Dean.

174
00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:26.833
We got two periods left.
Your turnovers are killing us.

175
00:08:26.916 --> 00:08:28.833
-Don't worry about us. We're good.
-[imitates buzzer]

176
00:08:28.916 --> 00:08:30.875
Fuck that. I'm not good.

177
00:08:30.958 --> 00:08:33.583
[Jensen] Let's just work as a team
and try not to do it all ourselves.

178
00:08:33.666 --> 00:08:36.375
-No more one-on-one sloppiness.
-I got it. okay? Fine.

179
00:08:36.458 --> 00:08:39.041
Hey. cut the attitude. Graham.

180
00:08:39.125 --> 00:08:40.208
I mean it.

181
00:08:43.916 --> 00:08:45.916
Hey. Delaney's trying
to take you out of the game.

182
00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:48.208
so take their defenders out. too.
As soon as the puck comes in.

183
00:08:48.291 --> 00:08:50.791
-you just get rid of it.
-Who died and made you coach?

184
00:08:50.875 --> 00:08:52.458
I'm out there. too. man.

185
00:08:52.541 --> 00:08:54.625
Okay. then worry about yourself.
all right?

186
00:08:54.708 --> 00:08:56.416
Okay. fine.

187
00:08:57.500 --> 00:08:59.333
I don't know what your problem is.

188
00:08:59.416 --> 00:09:02.458
but I suggest you do
whatever it takes to work it out.

189
00:09:02.541 --> 00:09:03.875
Fucking quick.

190
00:09:09.625 --> 00:09:11.291
[exhales heavily]

191
00:09:15.083 --> 00:09:16.500
[exhales]

192
00:09:20.041 --> 00:09:21.666
[phone line rings]

193
00:09:26.458 --> 00:09:27.875
[cell phone vibrating]

194
00:09:37.833 --> 00:09:39.833
[soft piano playing]

195
00:09:49.458 --> 00:09:51.458
[piano volume increases]

196
00:10:58.708 --> 00:10:59.708
[gasps]

197
00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:09.500
Sorry. Sorry. Uh...

198
00:11:09.583 --> 00:11:12.375
I-I couldn't be in my room. so I came.

199
00:11:12.458 --> 00:11:13.833
And I-I heard.

200
00:11:16.208 --> 00:11:18.208
Who was that you were playing?

201
00:11:18.875 --> 00:11:20.750
It's actually an original.

202
00:11:20.833 --> 00:11:25.291
Part of a series I wrote
when my son first went off to day care.

203
00:11:25.375 --> 00:11:26.500
[chuckles]

204
00:11:26.583 --> 00:11:29.333
Kind of exploring the emptiness of time.

205
00:11:29.416 --> 00:11:30.666
Wow. Y--

206
00:11:32.291 --> 00:11:34.000
-You're incredible.
-Ah.

207
00:11:34.083 --> 00:11:35.291
I would hope so.

208
00:11:35.375 --> 00:11:37.375
-[plays notes]
-That's why I'm here. right?

209
00:11:41.291 --> 00:11:42.291
You okay?

210
00:11:43.625 --> 00:11:45.250
Yeah. I finally get it.

211
00:11:45.958 --> 00:11:48.458
When you said.
"Write music that lets people in."

212
00:11:48.541 --> 00:11:52.791
Like. just now. I-I didn't know
it was about your son. but I felt it.

213
00:11:55.083 --> 00:11:56.958
That's a sweet compliment.

214
00:11:57.750 --> 00:12:00.791
Just having a hard time taking it.

215
00:12:00.875 --> 00:12:04.125
because of the general melancholy.

216
00:12:05.375 --> 00:12:07.083
Uh. it's...

217
00:12:07.166 --> 00:12:09.500
It's just that I don't think
I could ever write anything

218
00:12:09.583 --> 00:12:10.750
that comes close to doing that.

219
00:12:10.833 --> 00:12:13.166
-Come on. that's not true.
-No. it is.

220
00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:17.166
I-I can't do what you do.

221
00:12:18.125 --> 00:12:19.000
Letting people in.

222
00:12:19.083 --> 00:12:20.708
-Hannah--
-No. it's okay.

223
00:12:20.791 --> 00:12:24.375
Um. I made a mistake trying to do this.

224
00:12:24.458 --> 00:12:27.708
Anyway. uh. it's been an honor
to be a part of your class.

225
00:12:27.791 --> 00:12:29.291
I really hope we can keep in touch.

226
00:12:29.375 --> 00:12:32.625
Not on my student email.
because if I don't do the showcase.

227
00:12:32.708 --> 00:12:35.541
then I-- I won't be here
next semester. but. um...

228
00:12:35.625 --> 00:12:38.500
I'll send you my old one.
It's a Yahoo. for some reason.

229
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:39.791
[Daveed]
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Hold up.

230
00:12:39.875 --> 00:12:41.458
Hannah. Hannah. Hannah.
Hannah. Hannah.

231
00:12:41.541 --> 00:12:46.041
Just. if you don't come back here
right now. okay?

232
00:12:46.833 --> 00:12:51.500
I'm still your advisor for as long
as you're here. so. talk to me.

233
00:12:51.583 --> 00:12:53.750
Get your money's worth.
[exhales]

234
00:12:54.291 --> 00:12:56.208
I have been doing this a while.

235
00:12:59.416 --> 00:13:00.833
I mean...

236
00:13:02.250 --> 00:13:03.583
Like. doesn't it hurt?

237
00:13:04.458 --> 00:13:05.458
Doesn't what hurt?

238
00:13:06.666 --> 00:13:10.291
Ripping yourself open over and over again.

239
00:13:11.333 --> 00:13:14.625
Letting people see all the weird.
jagged pieces of you.

240
00:13:15.833 --> 00:13:17.083
Is that what it feels like?

241
00:13:17.166 --> 00:13:19.041
Yeah. well. it doesn't feel good.

242
00:13:20.291 --> 00:13:23.375
I don't subscribe to the notion
that art has to be painful.

243
00:13:23.458 --> 00:13:25.750
In fact. if done right.

244
00:13:25.833 --> 00:13:28.291
allowing people into our truth.

245
00:13:28.375 --> 00:13:29.958
that can even be healing.

246
00:13:30.041 --> 00:13:32.291
Yeah. I don't-- I don't know about that.

247
